node.text:
Making Tomato Sauce & Basic Pesto!
.
Basic Pesto:
1 cup basil
1 tbsp pine nuts
1 clove garlic 
1/4 cup olive oil
2 tbsp grated Parmesan cheese
Salt & pepper
Instructions:
Blend all ingredients in a food processor.
Tomato Sauce:
2 tbsp HIGH QUALITY olive oil
2 28 ounce cans whole peeled San Marzano tomatoes
4-5 cloves of garlic thinly sliced
3 springs of fresh basil
1 tbsp sugar or honey
Salt & pepper to taste
Heat olive oil in a sauce pan over medium heat. Add your garlic and sauté until fragrant, then add basil and stir to wilt it.
Add in your tomatoes and the sugar/honey.
Bring to a boil then let simmer anywhere from 30 minutes to all day! 
Remove the springs of basil with the exception of a few leaves for added flavor. Blend with an immersion blender for a smooth, creamy sauce.

Taco Tuesday starter kit today! Taco meat, fajita veggies, and MARGS! Recipes below.
.
Taco Meat:
1 lb grass fed ground beef (85% lean)
1 tsp chili powder
1 tsp cumin
1/2 tsp kosher salt
1/2 tsp pepper
1/2 tsp paprika
1/2 tsp garlic powder
1/4 tsp cayenne pepper
1/3 cup shredded Mexican cheese
Optional:
1/3 cup water
1 tsp tapioca flour or corn starch (or 1 tbsp regular flour)
Instructions:
Heat a skillet over medium heat. Once it’s hot, add in your ground beef. Break it up with a wooden spoon as it browns.
Once the meat is almost fully browned, add in seasonings. If you like more “saucy” beef, add in a slurry of flour + water and let it simmer on low heat until the liquid dissolved (6-8 minutes). 
Remove the beef from the heat and immediately stir in the shredded cheese. 
Serve with tortillas, in enchiladas, in my Crunchwrap recipe, the possibilities are endless! Makes 4 servings. 

Fajita Veggies:
1 yellow or red onion, sliced 
3 bell peppers, cut into slices 
2 cloves garlic, minced
2 tbsp avocado oil
1/2 tsp chili powder
1/2 tsp cumin
1/2 tsp kosher salt
1/2 tsp pepper
1/2 tsp paprika
1/2 tsp garlic powder
Juice from 1 lime
Instructions:
Heat a skillet over medium heat. Once hot, add avocado oil to the pan. Add in your veggies and seasonings. 
Saute for about 5-7 minutes, stirring every minute or so. Remove from heat, squeeze lime juice on top and serve! Makes about 4 servings. 

Margarita
2 oz Tequila
1 oz Triple Sec
Juice from 2 small limes
Splash of water (0.5 oz)
Ice
Salt or Tajin for the rim
Instructions:
Use a lime to wet the rim of the glass then coat in tajin or salt. 
Shake all ingredients together with ice. Pour over ice to serve. Makes 1 margarita.

4 Delicious Salad Dressings 🤍
.
Green Goddess
1/2 cup fresh parsley
1/2 cup fresh basil
2 cloves garlic
1 lemon juiced
1 tbsp red wine vinegar
2 tbsp olive oil
2 tbsp mayo Greek yogurt will work too
Pinch of kosher salt & pepper

Basic Vinaigrette 
1/4 cup olive oil
2 tbsp red wine vinegar
1 tsp Dijon mustard
1 clove garlic minced or crushed
1 tsp maple syrup (optional) 
Pinch of dried oregano salt & pepper

Healthy Homemade Ranch
1 cup Greek yogurt 1/2 tsp Kosher salt  ½ tsp black pepper 1 tsp garlic powder 1 tsp onion powder 1 tsp dried parsley ½ tsp dried dill 1-2 tbsp milk (I used unsweetened almond)

Skinny Caesar
1/3 cup Greek yogurt or hummus
1/2 lemon juice & zest
2 tsp Dijon mustard
1/2 tsp Worcestershire sauce
1 clove garlic minced
2 tbsp Pecorino or grated Parmesan cheese
Water or milk to thin out

node.text:
This week’s Back to the Basics is Potatoes 3 Ways because who doesn’t freaking LOVE potatoes?! They don’t need much to taste amazing and these 3 recipes prove it. What’s your favorite way to eat a potato?! 🥔🤍
.
Roasted Smashed Potatoes
Ingredients:
1 lb small white potatoes, peeled
1 tbsp olive oil 
1 tbsp fresh thyme 
4 garlic cloves, peeled and smashed
1 tsp kosher salt 
1/2 tsp black pepper 
Instructions:
Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Add potatoes to a large pot and fully cover with cold water. Bring to a boil and boil for 15 minutes until they start to get soft. 
Add to a baking dish and coat with olive oil, thyme, salt and pepper. Add in garlic cloves.
Bake for 30 minutes then smash the potatoes with a masher or the bottom of a cup. Bake for an additional 10 minutes. Top with more thyme, grated Parmesan and a drizzle of oil if needed.
.
Baked Potatoes
Ingredients: 
2 russet potatoes 
1 tbsp olive oil 
Kosher salt 
Toppings:
Sour cream or Greek yogurt
Chives
Bacon 
Shredded cheddar cheese 
Instructions:
Preheat oven to 350. Poke 6-8 holes in your potatoes with a fork. Coat your potatoes in olive oil and kosher salt. Place on the middle rack of the oven with a baking sheet below to catch any droppings. Bake for one hour or until potatoes are soft.
Cut in half and serve with desired toppings.
.
Baked French Fries
1 large russet potato
1 tbsp avocado oil
1/2 tsp garlic powder
1/2 tsp paprika
1/2 tsp kosher salt
1/2 tsp black pepper
1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese
Instructions
Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
Cut the russet potato in half short ways then cut each half into “fries” long ways. Place in a bowl of cold water and let them soak for 20-30 minutes.
Drain water, pat your fries fry and toss in avocado oil and seasonings.
Place on your baking sheet and bake for 20 minutes, flip, then continue baking for an additional 15 minutes or until golden and crispy.
Immediately after you remove the fries from the oven, generously sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Serve with ketchup or your favorite aioli.

It has been SUCH a stressful week you guys and I know a lot of you are feeling the chaotic energy! Wanted to share what I do to give myself a little extra love when I’m feeling down. Feel free to share what helps you in the comments 😘
✨ B vitamins! Research shows B vitamins can significantly improve your mood and reduce the physiological response to stress. @hiballenergy not only has B vitamins, but also organic caffeine to keep you energized 🧡 #ad
✨ Meditate. Even just 10 minutes makes such a difference!
✨ Read a book! Join #BroccsBookClub for the best reads. This month we are reading “Confess” by @colleenhoover.
✨ Get outside. Even if it’s just a quick walk around the block. 
✨ Put your phone away. Sometimes just an hour of “no phone time” makes me feel so much more centered. 
✨ Make a new recipe! You know I love cooking and it can sometimes feel therapeutic. Plus you get a delicious meal at the end. It’s a win win.
✨ Remember that these feelings are only temporary. Without the lows, we wouldn’t appreciate all the highs.

Peach & Burrata Crostini
Ingredients:
8-10 slices of a baguette, cut at a diagonal 
2-3 tbsp olive oil
1 garlic clove
6 oz burrata 
1 peach, cut into slices. I use @peaches.la_ peaches they’re the best!
4 oz prosciutto
1 tbsp fresh basil, chopped
Flakey sea salt, I use Maldon
Black pepper 
Balsamic glaze to top
Instructions:
Heat a skillet over medium heat. Add a generous drizzle of olive oil to the pan and carefully place in your bread. It should slowly turn golden brown after 3-4 minutes (if it starts to burn turn down the heat). Flip and cook for another 3ish minutes.
While the bread cooks, toss your peach slices in a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of flakey salt.
When the bread is done cooking, arrange it on a serving board. Scrape your garlic clove against the bread for flavor.
#broccyourbody #byb 
Add burrata, a peach slice, and prosciutto on each crostini. Top with balsamic glaze, basil, flakey salt and pepper.

One of my all time favorite dinners 😋 These Chimichurri Steak Bowls are inspired by one of my favorite spots in San Diego, @nectarinegrove. I always order this bowl for lunch when I’m there! The combo of flavors is just perfect 👏🏼 You must try! Skip the steak and use black beans for a vegetarian version.
.
Ingredients
Chimichurri Sauce:
1/2 cup cilantro, minced
1/4 cup flat leaf parsley, minced
2 cloves garlic, minced
1/3 jalapeño, minced
2 tbsp red wine vinegar
1/3 cup olive oil
Kosher salt & pepper
Flank Steak:
1-1.5 lbs flank steak
Kosher salt & pepper
Avocado oil
For the bowl:
Spinach
Brown rice
Sautéd onions
Sautéd zucchini
Roasted sweet potatoes
Goat cheese
Crushed plantain chips
Instructions
Combine all ingredients for the Chimichurri (make sure everything is finely minced!).
For the steak, season generously with kosher salt and pepper bring to room temperature. 
Heat a cast iron skillet over medium heat and add a drizzle of avocado oil. Depending on the thickness of the steak and how you like it cooked, let it cook for about 7-10 minutes each side. Let rest then cut into bit sized pieces. If it’s too rare, cut it up and add back into the pan to crisp it up!
Arrange your bowls! Add spinach, brown rice, onions, zucchini, potatoes, steak, Chimichurri, goat cheese and chips.
#broccyourbody #byb #easyrecipes #mealpreprecipes

I can’t be the only person who craves soup when it’s 85 degrees outside, right? Especially my Greek-Style Lemon Chicken Soup 😋 It truly NEVER gets old! I play around with the soup a lot by adding different veggies, swapping the orzo for rice or pasta, sometimes I even do a vegetarian version (on my blog), and every single time it just gets better and better. Don’t even get me started on the leftovers 🔥 Make sure you make this if you haven’t already, you won’t regret it!
.
Ingredients:
2 chicken breasts
8 cups chicken broth
1/2 white onion, diced
4 cloves garlic, crushed/diced
3 carrots, chopped
3-4 celery stalks, chopped
2 small zucchini, chopped
1 cup cauliflower rice
1 cup uncooked orzo or rice (this time I used egg noodles- any carb can really do the trick)
2-3 tbsp fresh dill and parsley (+ more to serve)
3 egg yolks
2 lemons
2 tbsp olive oil (+ more to serve)
2 tsp dried oregano
1 tsp salt & pepper (+ more to taste)
Instructions:
Sauté white onion, carrot and garlic in 2 tbsp olive oil over medium heat in a large soup pot or Dutch oven (InstantPot instructions available on the blog). Add in zucchini and cauliflower rice.
Make space for the chicken breasts and sear for 2-3 minutes each side. Add the chicken broth, fresh dill and parsley, oregano and salt & pepper. If you’re using rice instead of orzo, add it in now. Bring to a boil then turn heat low to simmer and cook covered for 30 minutes. 
If using orzo or pasta, add it in and let it simmer until it’s cooked through for the last 10 minutes.
Once the soup is done and the chicken is cooked through, set aside 1 cup of hot broth and slowly add it to your egg yolks (1 tbsp at a time) while whisking vigorously. This prevents the eggs from scrambling when you add it to the soup! 
Remove the chicken, shred it and add back in with the juice from the lemons and the egg yolk mixture.
Add more salt and pepper to taste. Serve with fresh parsley and dill and drizzle with a little olive oil! Makes 6 servings. #broccyourbody #byb #summersoup #healthyrecipes #easyrecipes

Had fish tacos for dinner last night and haven’t stopped thinking about them since. Picked up everything to make my BLACKENED FISH TACOS so I can relive my dinner again this weekend 🌮  These are SO easy to make (as always) and are the perfect summer dish! They won’t disappoint.
.
Ingredients:
Fish Tacos:
1 lb white fish we used cod
1/2 lime, juiced
1/2 tsp salt, pepper, garlic powder, cumin, chili powder, & paprika
Dash of cayenne
Avocado oil
8 tortillas we used @sietefoods cassava tortillas
Toppings:
1 cup slaw mix + 1-2 tbsp ranch dressing
Guacamole
Salsa
Greek yogurt
Lime wedges
Hot sauce
Instructions:
Cut your fish into long, thin filets. Squeeze lime juice into the fish and then coat both sides with the seasoning. 
Cook in a hot skillet over medium heat for 4-6 minutes each side, depending on the thickness of the fish. 
Heat your tortillas on a hot skillet for a few seconds each side. Assemble your tacos to your liking and serve!
Makes about 4 servings.

I honestly think this Coconut Lime Chicken is one of the best things I’ve ever made. I first posted it YEARS ago and have made it so many times since, not only with chicken but shrimp, tofu and even just veggies as a side. As long as there is sauce + rice to soak it up, I’m in heaven. Please make it ASAP 🙏🏼
.
Ingredients:
2 chicken breasts, cut longways to make them thinner
1-2 tbsp coconut oil
1 can coconut milk, just the solid top part
1 shallot, minced
1 clove garlic, minced
3 limes
2 tbsp cilantro
1 tsp turmeric
1/2 tsp red chili flakes
Kosher salt & pepper
Instructions:
Cut the chicken breasts in half longways and season with salt & peoper. Sear in coconut oil on medium high heat for about 4-5 minutes each side. Remove chicken from the pan and reduce heat to medium. 
Add in the shallot, garlic, and a little more coconut oil. Sauté until fragrant/soft.
Add in the cream (solidified top part) of the canned coconut milk, juice from the limes, cilantro, and salt, pepper, turmeric, & red chili flakes.
Add chicken back in and simmer for a couple minutes.
Top with red chili flakes for added spice and serve with rice. I did half regular rice and half cauliflower rice. I added some peas, cilantro and lime juice too 😋 Makes 4 servings.
#broccyourbody #byb #healthyrecipes #mealpreprecipes #easyrecipes

NO COOKING REQUIRED healthy dinner 👏🏼 Look, I love cooking but sometimes I am straight up not in the mood. This version of the Le Bowl requires minimal effort and no actual cooking at all. Clearly it’s become a weeknight staple… ENJOY! 
.
Ingredients:
4 oz rotisserie chicken, shredded
1 cup arugula
1/3 cup brown rice
Small handful of cherry tomatoes
1/2 avocado
Parmesan cheese
Black pepper
Sriracha “Mayo:”
1/3 cup Greek yogurt or Mayo
1 tbsp sriracha
1 tbsp sesame oil
1 tbsp water
Instructions:
Whisk together all ingredients for the sriracha Mayo. Add water as needed for thickness (should be a dressing consistency).
Layer the bowl in order: arugula, brown rice, tomatoes, avocado, chicken, cheese then drizzle with sauce. Makes 1 bowl with leftover sriracha mayo!
#broccyourbody #byb #healthyrecipes #easyrecipes #weeknightrecipes #mealpreprecipes

Pasta Sunday 🍋🍝 This Lemony + Cheesy Pasta is the most perfect pasta dish for summer. It’s extremely simple to make but it’s honestly one of my all time favorite recipes. Made a simple salad as a side and it was just perfection 🤌🏼
.
Ingredients:
12 oz pasta, I used fresh spaghetti from @eatalyla 
1 lemon, juiced and zested (I finish it off with more lemon juice because I love lots of lemon!)
1 cup Pecorino cheese, (finely grated Parmesan will work too, just make sure you grate it fresh!)
4 tbsp salted butter
Freshly cracked black pepper
Kosher salt
Red chili flakes
Fresh parsley to serve
Ingredients:
Cook your pasta according to the package- do not strain it (you’ll be removing the pasta directly from the water it was cooked in to the pan with the sauce to help the it stick better). Don’t forget to generously salt your pasta water!
In a medium sized bowl, whisk together the grated cheese, lemon zest, and slowly add in pasta water to create a thick creamy paste. Set aside.
Heat a large saucepan over medium heat and add about 1 tsp of black pepper and butter. Once the butter is melted, add about 1/3 cup pasta water to the pan.
Using tongs, add the pasta straight from the water it was cooked in to the pan. Add in the cheese sauce from earlier and combine. Season with salt, pepper, and red chili flakes. Add more pasta water if the pasta looks dry.
Remove from heat and add the lemon juice. Stir to combine and season to taste. Serve with fresh parsley and more cheese.
#broccyourbody #byb #easyrecipes #lemonpasta

Nothing says summer like a creamy COCONUT MARG 🥥 It literally tastes like being on a tropical vacation. You must make ASAP!
Top: @shopvandevort 
Jeans: @agolde 
Serving board: @tulip_haus 
. 
Ingredients for 2 cocktails:
3 oz tequila, I always use @casamigos 
2 oz @cointreau_us or triple sec
4 oz canned coconut milk
4 limes
Ice
For the rim:
Maple syrup 
Coconut shreds, chopped
Instructions:
Heat a skillet over medium heat and add your coconut shreds. Stir around until golden brown and toasted.
Add two handfuls of ice to a cocktail shaker. Add tequila, Cointreau, coconut milk (shake well before opening) and lime juice. Shake for about a minute.
Assemble your glasses by coating the rim in maple syrup then toasted coconut shreds.
Add ice, strain the coconut margarita into each glass and garnish with a slice of lime.
#broccyourbody #byb #coconutmargarita #summercocktail #easyrecipes
